<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>8 SPEED, 9 SPEED, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the hub of the auxiliary drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018j2">Figure 192</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018j2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018j2" filename="../figg13/G13018J2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 191. Remove Snap Ring From Hub of Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the rear face of the retainer ring as a base and press the drive gear through the
                bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018j3">Figure 193</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018j3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018j3" filename="../figg13/G13018J3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 192. Press Drive Gear Through Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, remove the O-rings from the hub O.D. of the front auxiliary drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018j4">Figure 194</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018j4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018j4" filename="../figg13/G13018J4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 193. Remove O-Rings From Hub O.D. of Front Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
